108
00:09:24,959 --> 00:09:29,781
[SPEAKER_05]: I'm genuinely confused about the content posted in the notice of demolition review public hearing.

109
00:09:30,282 --> 00:09:40,787
[SPEAKER_05]: The notice includes a description of work stating what is planned is interior and exterior renovation, but the statement to the right of that text describes the action as an intent to demolish a significant building.

110
00:09:41,407 --> 00:09:49,491
[SPEAKER_05]: I suppose one could infer given the stated description of work that the planned demolition must be selective and partial, but that is not 100% clear.

111
00:09:50,011 --> 00:09:51,832
[SPEAKER_05]: If that is indeed correct, however,

112
00:09:52,228 --> 00:10:00,475
[SPEAKER_05]: then it seems appropriate as, for example, the porch of the house at 28 Grove Street is clearly not salvageable and should be demolished down to the stone foundation.

113
00:10:01,096 --> 00:10:04,198
[SPEAKER_05]: Other exterior elements would also require removal and replacement.

114
00:10:04,679 --> 00:10:08,863
[SPEAKER_05]: On the other hand, if there is an intent to demolish the building entirely, that would be troubling.

115
00:10:09,143 --> 00:10:19,392
[SPEAKER_05]: I'd be opposed to the full demolition and replacement as rehab of the existing structure seems far more appropriate and likely to preserve the character of both this property and the surrounding community.

116
00:10:21,068 --> 00:10:23,470
[SPEAKER_05]: That was David here at 25 Grove Street.

117
00:10:30,336 --> 00:10:30,676
[SPEAKER_02]: Okay.

118
00:10:32,237 --> 00:10:37,061
