[SPEAKER_05]: Thank you for coming.

128
00:11:24,796 --> 00:11:26,256
[SPEAKER_09]: Good evening, everyone.

129
00:11:27,496 --> 00:11:34,578
[SPEAKER_09]: So I'm glad to see all of our neighbors have responded to the hearing post in front of the house.

130
00:11:35,418 --> 00:11:37,859
[SPEAKER_09]: And just a few things I want to highlight.

131
00:11:38,879 --> 00:11:40,280
[SPEAKER_09]: So the intent of this

132
00:11:42,200 --> 00:11:47,642
[SPEAKER_09]: The intent we have for this house is not torn down the house and build a super modern one.

133
00:11:48,202 --> 00:11:51,323
[SPEAKER_09]: So the intent that we have is basically restore the house.

134
00:11:52,143 --> 00:11:55,684
[SPEAKER_09]: I can give it a refresh and basically bring everything to the code.

135
00:11:56,405 --> 00:12:03,187
[SPEAKER_09]: So the only exterior change we are proposing is to have a tiny kitchen extension at the back of the house.

136
00:12:03,674 --> 00:12:05,897
[SPEAKER_09]: and a slightly bigger dorm at the back of the roof.

137
00:12:06,497 --> 00:12:13,446
[SPEAKER_09]: Basically, all other three sides of the building, it remains largely untouched, I would say.

138
00:12:14,347 --> 00:12:19,493
[SPEAKER_09]: Even most of the window openings remains the same.

139
00:12:20,213 --> 00:12:22,897
[SPEAKER_09]: And as some of the neighbors mentioned,

140
00:12:23,738 --> 00:12:35,312
